00:12:58.385 --> 00:13:00.721
Look at this,all these melons, no good.
你看，种的全是甜瓜，一点儿用处都没有。


181
00:13:00.888 --> 00:13:03.765
Spoiled. Hog food now.
又不能吃。还不如拿来养猪。


182
00:13:03.932 --> 00:13:07.644
Jewel, darlin',you got to throw these out.
朱厄尔，亲爱的，你把这些扔出去。


183
00:13:07.811 --> 00:13:10.272
You got some.45 shells?
你有点45的子弹吗？


184
00:13:13.650 --> 00:13:15.110
Clean out.
卖光了。


185
00:13:15.277 --> 00:13:17.429
Be going to Gainesville first thing in the morning.
明早第一件事就是去盖恩斯维尔。


186
00:13:17.696 --> 00:13:20.157
I'll pick some up.You still be around then?
我去进一些货。如果那时你还在的话？


187
00:13:20.324 --> 00:13:22.701
Might be.
也许吧。


188
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:31.502
What's wrong with you two today?
你们两个今天是怎么回事？


189
00:13:31.668 --> 00:13:33.504
Every time I try to tell you to do something,
每次我想让你俩做什么，


190
00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:35.005
you won't listen.
你们都不听。


191
00:13:35.172 --> 00:13:36.607
You know, I will smack you.I'll smack you.
听着，我要揍们。


192
00:13:36.673 --> 00:13:38.592
No more playtime for you, none.Not today.
别再求我，今天不管用。


193
00:13:42.679 --> 00:13:44.515
Mornin', teacher, ma'am.
早上好，老师，夫人。


194
00:13:44.681 --> 00:13:46.141
I wonder if you can tell me...
你能告诉我...


195
00:13:46.308 --> 00:13:48.310
where a man can find hisself a good meal?
哪儿有饭吃？


196
00:13:50.145 --> 00:13:51.814
Y'all go inside.
你俩进屋去。


197
00:13:54.149 --> 00:13:57.486
Well, my name ain't "teacher, ma'am." It's Beulah.
我的名字不叫“老师，夫人”，我叫比乌拉。


198
00:13:57.653 --> 00:14:00.030
Folks I know call me Scrappie.
认识我的人叫我“斯卡比”。


199
00:14:02.366 --> 00:14:05.661
Well, folks I know call me Mann...
那好，认识我的人叫我“曼恩...”


200
00:14:07.371 --> 00:14:08.664
Miss Scrappie.
斯卡比小姐。


201
00:14:11.708 --> 00:14:13.710
Nice to meet you, Mr. Mann.
很高兴认识你，曼恩先生。


202
00:14:13.877 --> 00:14:15.129
Likewise.
我也是。


203
00:14:20.175 --> 00:14:22.052
Now, this here Rattler,Mr. Mann.
曼恩先生，它叫“响尾蛇”。


204
00:14:22.219 --> 00:14:23.554
He a deer dog.
他是一条鹿犬。


205
00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:24.888
He help me hunt,
他帮我打猎，


206
00:14:25.055 --> 00:14:27.724
'cause he can get real quiet,know what I mean?
因为他很安静，明白我的意思吗?


207
00:14:27.891 --> 00:14:29.726
All right, come on, boy.
好了，来吧，小子。


208
00:14:29.893 --> 00:14:31.770
This way now. This way.
这边来，这边。


209
00:14:35.732 --> 00:14:38.068
So, what, uh,
呃，那什么，


210
00:14:38.235 --> 00:14:40.212
what you selling now,Mr. Mann?
你现在推销什么呢？曼恩先生。


211
00:14:40.279 --> 00:14:43.782
What makes you think I'm selling something, Mr. Carrier?
你凭什么认为我在卖东西，开利先生？


212
00:14:43.949 --> 00:14:49.288
Well, I figure a colored fellow with nowhere particular to be,
好吧，我想一个没有什么特殊身份的有色人种，


213
00:14:49.455 --> 00:14:51.665
that man be sellin' something...
那他一定是在卖东西…


214
00:14:52.958 --> 00:14:55.544
or he runnin'.
或者他在逃跑。


215
00:14:59.256 --> 00:15:00.757
Well...
那么...


216
00:15:00.924 --> 00:15:02.551
you figure wrong...
你搞错了...


217
00:15:03.886 --> 00:15:05.220
friend.
交个朋友。


218
00:15:13.228 --> 00:15:14.688
Come on inside.
进屋吧。


219
00:15:17.775 --> 00:15:20.778
Hey, Gertie,got some good news.
嘿，葛蒂，有个好消息。


220
00:15:20.986 --> 00:15:23.071
Mr. Mann here ain't sellin' nothin'.
曼恩先生什么也不推销。


221
00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:25.616
Turn that music down.
把音乐声关小一点儿。


222
00:15:25.783 --> 00:15:28.243
My husband got a suspicious mind.
我丈夫总是疑神疑鬼。


223
00:15:28.452 --> 00:15:29.912
Oh, yes, I do.
哦，我是这样的。


224
00:15:31.455 --> 00:15:33.081
He's sweet on you.
他看上你了。


225
00:15:33.248 --> 00:15:35.317
Scrappie, come over here and help me with this bird.
斯卡比，过来帮我端出这只烤火鸡。


226
00:15:36.752 --> 00:15:38.128
Must be New Year's.
一定是到了新年了。


227
00:15:38.295 --> 00:15:40.297
Yes, sir.Come on in, Mr. Mann.
是的，先生。进来吧，曼恩先生。


228
00:15:45.594 --> 00:15:47.262
Evenin', Mr. Mann.
晚上好，曼恩先生生。


229
00:15:47.429 --> 00:15:48.764
Ma'am.
夫人。


230
00:15:48.931 --> 00:15:50.265
Thank you.
谢谢你。


231
00:15:50.432 --> 00:15:52.643
This is my brother James,
这是我的兄弟詹姆斯，


232
00:15:52.810 --> 00:15:55.938
his wife Emma, and their daughter Jewel.
这是他的妻子，艾玛，还有他们的女儿，朱维尔。


233
00:15:58.190 --> 00:16:00.109
Be quiet.
安静点儿。


234
00:16:00.275 --> 00:16:02.861
Scrappie, show the man a seat.
斯卡比，为客人准备座位。


235
00:16:04.363 --> 00:16:05.948
You can sit here.
你可以坐在这里。


236
00:16:06.949 --> 00:16:08.450
Thank you.
谢谢你。


237
00:16:15.958 --> 00:16:17.292
Scrappie!
斯卡比！


238
00:16:18.419 --> 00:16:20.979
Now, I had a talk with Mr. Andrews...
跟你说，我今天和安德鲁斯先生谈了...


239
00:16:21.046 --> 00:16:23.132
on your behalf today.
为了你的利益。


240
00:16:23.340 --> 00:16:25.008
What about Mr. Andrews?
安德鲁斯先生怎么了？


241
00:16:25.217 --> 00:16:26.385
Mama, that old cracker...
妈妈，我正撞见那个老坏蛋...


242
00:16:26.468 --> 00:16:28.303
caught hisself whistling at Scrappie and all that.
冲着斯卡比吹口哨来着。


243
00:16:28.470 --> 00:16:29.471
What?
什么？


244
00:16:29.638 --> 00:16:30.681
Yeah, that's right.
是的，就是那样。


245
00:16:30.848 --> 00:16:33.074
I went over there and gave him some words.
我过去跟他理论了几句。


246
00:16:34.351 --> 00:16:37.312
Sylvester, what you say to them people now?
希尔维斯特，你现在想说什么？


247
00:16:38.397 --> 00:16:43.193
Mr. Andrews, I come to have a word with you about my cousin.
安德鲁斯先生，我来跟你谈谈我表妹的事。


248
00:16:43.360 --> 00:16:46.947
Now, I expect you to show her some respect.
从现在起，我希望你能尊重她。


249
00:16:47.114 --> 00:16:49.491
You expect, boy?
小子，这就是你想的？


250
00:16:50.909 --> 00:16:53.829
I don't like Scrappie feelin' scared around nobody.
我不喜欢斯卡比在别人面前感到害怕。


251
00:16:53.996 --> 00:16:56.415
That a threat?
这是在威胁吗？


252
00:16:59.877 --> 00:17:02.212
Ain't no threat needed.
不需要威胁。


253
00:17:02.379 --> 00:17:05.215
I'm just sayin' I don't mess with your peoples,
我只是说，我不会惹你的人，


254
00:17:05.382 --> 00:17:08.218
I don't want you messin' with mines.
我也不想你惹我的人。


255
00:17:08.385 --> 00:17:11.421
Now, I thank you very kindly, sir.
现在，我认为你还是个很好的人，先生。


256
00:17:12.473 --> 00:17:16.310
Sylvester, you can't talk to white folks like that...
希尔维斯特，你不能这样对白人说话...


257
00:17:16.477 --> 00:17:18.412
and not expect a rope around your neck.
除非你想被绞死。


258
00:17:18.479 --> 00:17:20.314
Look, times is changin', Mama.
你看，妈妈，时代已经变了。


259
00:17:20.481 --> 00:17:22.357
Now, I ain't no sharecropper.
我不是佃农了。


260
00:17:22.524 --> 00:17:24.151
I'm a music teacher.
我是个音乐教师。


261
00:17:24.318 --> 00:17:28.363
Times ain't never changed for no crackers, boy.
那些坏蛋可没随着时代而改变，孩子。


262
00:17:28.530 --> 00:17:31.533
Don't you forget they burned a colored man...
别忘了，他们去年夏天还烧死过一个黑人…


263
00:17:31.742 --> 00:17:35.204
over in Wylie last summer for winking at a white woman.
就因为他在怀利镇，对一个白娘儿们抛了个媚眼儿。


264
00:17:35.412 --> 00:17:36.371
Sure did.
真是这样的。


265
00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:37.915
I know that, Mama,
那件事我知道，妈妈，


266
00:17:38.081 --> 00:17:40.017
but it's all right for them to whistle at Scrappie?
但他们就可以对着斯卡比吹口哨吗？


267
00:17:40.083 --> 00:17:41.460
No, that ain't right.
不，那样做也不对。


268
00:17:46.381 --> 00:17:48.717
What do you think about all this business, Mr. Mann?
曼恩先生，你对这件事情怎么看？


269
00:17:48.884 --> 00:17:51.428
Oh, that man ready to eat.
哦，让人家吃饭吧。


270
00:17:51.595 --> 00:17:54.556
Would you like to say the blessing, Mr. Mann?
你想为我们念祝祷辞吗？曼恩先生。


271
00:17:54.723 --> 00:17:56.183
No, ma'am.
不了，夫人。


272
00:17:56.350 --> 00:17:58.310
I'll do it, Mama.I'll do it.
我来吧，妈妈。还是让我来吧。


273
00:18:01.313 --> 00:18:04.483
Thank you for the bounty of our lives...
感谢你赐予我们生命...


274
00:18:04.650 --> 00:18:06.902
and the blessings you've bestowed on us...
感谢你赐予我们...


275
00:18:07.069 --> 00:18:08.570
at home and family.
我们家的每个人。


276
00:18:11.073 --> 00:18:12.825
Can I have my yams now?
我现在可以吃番薯了吗？


277
00:18:14.743 --> 00:18:16.578
Who wants ham?
谁想要火腿？


278
00:18:16.745 --> 00:18:18.580
I want some yams.
我想要点儿番薯。


279
00:18:18.747 --> 00:18:21.083
Scrappie,come eat a part of the bird...
斯卡比，过来分这只火鸡...


280
00:18:21.250 --> 00:18:22.751
that went over the fence last.
它差点儿就飞过篱笆。


281
00:18:29.591 --> 00:18:32.803
Well, at least ask him...all right, all right.
好吧，至少问问他…好吧，好吧。


282
00:18:35.264 --> 00:18:39.435
Ma'am, I ain't had a supper like that in a long time.
夫人，我好久没吃过这样的晚餐了。


283
00:18:39.601 --> 00:18:41.353
Thank you kindly.
谢谢你们的好意。


284
00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:43.105
You're welcome.
你不用客气。


285
00:18:43.272 --> 00:18:45.774
You been drifting long,Mr. Mann?
你已经漂泊很久了吧？曼恩先生。


286
00:18:45.941 --> 00:18:47.609
Seem like forever.
似乎要一直这样了。


287
00:18:47.776 --> 00:18:50.112
That ain't no kind of life for a man.
那不是男人该过的生活。


288
00:18:50.279 --> 00:18:53.115
You get yourself a good piece of land,
你应该找块好地，


289
00:18:53.282 --> 00:18:55.217
the right woman...
找个合适的女人…


290
00:18:55.284 --> 00:18:57.119
a man can make a new start 'round here,
一个人可以在这里重新开始，


291
00:18:57.286 --> 00:18:58.996
make something of hisself.
开始他自己的生活。


292
00:18:59.163 --> 00:19:01.540
Ain't that right,Scrappie?
不是吗？斯卡比？


293
00:19:03.500 --> 00:19:08.422
Well, Aunt Sarah think Rosewood colored folks' heaven on earth.
莎拉阿姨认为，紫檀镇是人间天堂。


294
00:19:08.589 --> 00:19:11.633
Best place these old eyes ever seen.
这是我见过的最好的地方。


295
00:19:11.800 --> 00:19:14.803
Colored folks own all the land around here.
这里所有的土地都是黑人的。


296
00:19:14.970 --> 00:19:16.305
All the businesses, too,
所有的生意也是。


297
00:19:16.472 --> 00:19:18.807
except for Mr. Johnny Wright's store,
除了约翰尼.赖特的杂货店，


298
00:19:18.974 --> 00:19:21.310
and he a halfway decent white man,
他还是个正派的白人，


299
00:19:21.477 --> 00:19:23.687
if there ever was such a thing.
如果真有这种事的话。


300
00:19:23.896 --> 00:19:27.775
Most of us doin' better than them folks over in Sumner.
我们大多数人都比萨姆纳那边的人过得好。


301
00:19:27.941 --> 00:19:31.278
You ever seen a place like Rosewood, Mr. Mann?
你见过紫檀镇这样的地方吗？曼恩先生？


302
00:19:34.823 --> 00:19:36.241
No, ma'am.
没有，夫人。


303
00:19:52.424 --> 00:19:56.678
"Well, we know how to get money when we need some," said Pecos.
佩科斯说:“当我们需要钱的时候，我们知道如何弄到钱。”


304
00:19:56.845 --> 00:19:59.139
"All right," nodded Essex.
“好吧，”埃塞克斯点点头。


305
00:19:59.306 --> 00:20:01.642
"That's fine.
“这很好。”


306
00:20:01.809 --> 00:20:04.144
"But don't tell anybody I told you...
“但是别跟别人说,我告诉你的话...”


307
00:20:04.311 --> 00:20:06.772
"or I'll cut off your ears."
"否则，我就割下你的耳朵。"


308
00:20:08.273 --> 00:20:10.609
He's a tough character, Essex.
他可真是个狠角色，埃塞克斯。


309
00:20:10.776 --> 00:20:13.612
"Well, cross my heart and hope you die,"
“好吧，我发誓，希望你死，”


310
00:20:13.779 --> 00:20:14.988
replied Lightning fervently.
闪电热切地回答。


311
00:20:15.155 --> 00:20:17.199
"Well, that's fine,"replied Essex.
“那么，这样很好，”埃塞克斯回答道。


312
00:20:17.366 --> 00:20:19.952
"Now, go home and shut up."
“现在，回家去，很么都不许说。”


313
00:20:21.662 --> 00:20:23.789
"Or lose your ears,"added Thunder.
“不然就丢了耳朵。”鸣雷补充道。


314
00:20:25.165 --> 00:20:29.002
And that's it.Next chapter next week.
就是这样。下一章，下周再读。


315
00:20:29.169 --> 00:20:33.173
I'm going up Sumner, buying a drink for some of the boys.
我要去萨姆纳，给几个小伙子买杯喝的。


316
00:20:33.340 --> 00:20:35.717
John, I was thinking we might read aloud...
约翰，我想我们可以大声朗读…


317
00:20:35.884 --> 00:20:37.678
from the Good Book tonight.
《圣经》里的故事。


318
00:20:37.845 --> 00:20:40.722
It'll still be good tomorrow.
那就明天念吧。


319
00:20:40.889 --> 00:20:43.725
All right, boys, up to bed.
好了，孩子们，上床睡觉。


320
00:20:43.892 --> 00:20:45.227
Dad, come on.
爸爸，接着念吧。


321
00:20:45.394 --> 00:20:46.828
Dad, could we please stay up just a few more minutes?
爸爸，我们还能再留一小会儿吗？


322
00:20:46.895 --> 00:20:48.814
Best do what your ma says.
最好按你们妈妈说的去做。


323
00:20:53.402 --> 00:20:55.237
She ain't my ma.
她不是我妈妈。


324
00:20:55.404 --> 00:20:56.547
Timothy.
提摩西。


325
00:20:56.655 --> 00:20:59.199
What'd you say?
你说什么？


326
00:20:59.366 --> 00:21:01.426
What'd you say, Timothy?
你说了什么？提摩西？


327
00:21:02.411 --> 00:21:03.745
What was that for?
这是为什么？


328
00:21:03.912 --> 00:21:05.914
That's so you don't get to thinking like your brother.
这样，你才不会有你哥哥那样的想法。


329
00:21:06.081 --> 00:21:07.749
Get on to bed now.
现在就上床睡觉。


330
00:21:07.916 --> 00:21:09.460
Get on to bed!
睡觉去！


331
00:21:13.422 --> 00:21:15.632
Sorry about that, Mary, love.
很遗憾发生了这个，玛丽，我亲爱的。


332
00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:20.095
I guess the boys still miss her.
我想孩子们还在怀念他们的亲生母亲。


333
00:21:20.262 --> 00:21:22.181
You do, too, I reckon.
我认为，你也有点儿。


334
00:21:24.099 --> 00:21:27.269
You're damn right I miss her. Pardon me.
你说得对，我也想她。请原谅我。


335
00:21:27.436 --> 00:21:31.523
Only natural. Only been gone 7 months... 7 months, 3 days.
这是自然的。才走了7个月…7个月零3天。


336
00:21:36.945 --> 00:21:39.281
I'm going to that auction tomorrow.
我明天要去拍卖会。


337
00:21:39.448 --> 00:21:41.909
Get that plot of land.
买下那块地。


338
00:21:42.075 --> 00:21:43.760
Does that mean we're staying, then?
那就是说我们要留下了，然后呢？


339
00:21:43.827 --> 00:21:45.287
Ain't no sense of moving away.
离开没有任何意义。


340
00:21:45.454 --> 00:21:48.290
I get Bradley's 5 acres, build some bins out back, sell feed.
我得到布拉德利的五英亩地，在后院建一些货箱，卖饲料。


341
00:21:48.457 --> 00:21:49.792
Make enough money, in a few years,
几年后，就能挣下不少钱，


342
00:21:49.958 --> 00:21:51.335
we'll move to Gainesville,
我们将搬到盖恩斯维尔，


343
00:21:51.502 --> 00:21:55.297
open a bigger store, biggest they ever seen in Florida.
开一家在佛罗里达最大的商店。


344
00:21:55.464 --> 00:21:58.634
Did you ever consider how I feel living here?
你有没有想过，我住在这里是什么感觉？


345
00:22:14.316 --> 00:22:16.902
Why don't you go on and have that drink?
你为什么不去喝一杯呢？


346
00:22:21.490 --> 00:22:24.243
You be all right alone here New Year's?
你独自在家里过元旦，没事吗？


347
00:22:29.581 --> 00:22:31.708
I got Jesus with me.
我有上帝陪伴我。


348
00:22:49.518 --> 00:22:50.978
Go ahead.
去吧。


349
00:22:51.145 --> 00:22:53.063
There he is.
他就在那儿。


350
00:22:55.899 --> 00:22:57.359
Gertie looks good.
葛蒂看起来很好。


351
00:22:59.445 --> 00:23:00.779
Watch yourself, there, Carter.
看你自己，那儿，卡特。


352
00:23:00.946 --> 00:23:02.948
Watch yourself there.
看你自己。


353
00:23:03.115 --> 00:23:05.451
I'm gonna cut a rug.
我要跳摇摆舞。


354
00:23:05.617 --> 00:23:07.453
Cut a rug.
摇摆舞。


355
00:23:07.619 --> 00:23:10.981
Go on, cut that rug, but don't cut it too deep.
继续，摇摆去吧，但别太嗨了。


356
00:23:30.976 --> 00:23:32.561
Come on.
来吧。


357
00:23:35.481 --> 00:23:37.775
Dance like he's riding Booker T.
像他骑着布克·T一样跳舞。


358
00:23:44.531 --> 00:23:46.700
Twirl that man, Scrappie.
转晕那家伙，斯卡比。


359
00:23:51.497 --> 00:23:53.332
Listen here, now.Y'all take notes, all right?
听到这里,现在。你们都应记笔记，对吧？


360
00:23:53.499 --> 00:23:55.334
I don't want to have to do this more than once.
我不想再说第二遍了


361
00:23:55.501 --> 00:23:57.795
Come on, man,show him how to do it.
来吧，哥们，教他们怎么做。


362
00:24:13.268 --> 00:24:14.812
Sylvester can't do no dancing.
西尔韦斯特不跳舞就受不了。


363
00:24:18.107 --> 00:24:19.942
Africa.
非洲。


364
00:24:20.109 --> 00:24:21.944
Africa.
非洲。


365
00:24:22.111 --> 00:24:23.153
Nigerian.
尼日利亚人。


366
00:24:36.340 --> 00:24:40.340
星期五

367
00:24:43.340 --> 00:24:45.676
My arm! My arm! My arm! My arm!
我的胳膊！我的胳膊！我的胳膊！


368
00:24:45.843 --> 00:24:47.469
I got you. I got you.
我抓住你了。我抓住了你。


369
00:25:09.199 --> 00:25:11.034
I... I brung you some coffee.
我...我给你拿来些咖啡。


370
00:25:13.370 --> 00:25:15.164
I'm sorry.
对不起。


371
00:25:17.916 --> 00:25:19.877
It's all right.
没关系的。


372
00:25:20.043 --> 00:25:23.005
I shouldn't have snuck up on you.
我不该偷偷接近你的。


373
00:25:26.550 --> 00:25:28.051
You ridin' out today?
你今天要出去吗？


374
00:25:32.222 --> 00:25:36.059
I might be here a couple more days anyway.
我可能还要在这里呆几天。


375
00:25:36.268 --> 00:25:40.105
Thinkin' about lookin' in on that piece of land over there.
想去看看那边的那块拍卖地。


376
00:25:45.903 --> 00:25:47.863
Bye.
再见。


377
00:25:59.958 --> 00:26:01.794
Mornin', Mr. Mann.
早上好，曼恩先生。


378
00:26:01.960 --> 00:26:03.337
Mornin', boy.
早安，孩子。


379
00:26:03.504 --> 00:26:06.256
Tomorrow's my birthday.You gonna come to my party?
明天是我的生日，记得要来参加聚会。


380
00:26:06.465 --> 00:26:07.883
You gonna have cake?
你会有蛋糕吗？


381
00:26:08.050 --> 00:26:10.135
Yes, sir, chocolate.
是的，先生，巧克力的。


382
00:26:10.302 --> 00:26:12.429
Why is she skippin'?
她跑什么？


383
00:26:14.598 --> 00:26:15.891
Good coffee.
很棒的咖啡。


384
00:26:33.450 --> 00:26:35.202
Morning, Mr. Mann.
早上好，曼恩先生。


385
00:26:36.086 --> 00:26:39.156
Small town, people talk.
这小镇子上，人们都说起了你。


386
00:26:39.341 --> 00:26:42.417
Old hangover remedy.
这是解决宿醉的老偏方儿。


387
00:26:42.584 --> 00:26:44.669
My granddaddy taught me.
我的爷爷教会我做的。


388
00:26:45.796 --> 00:26:47.589
Here's to the new year.
今天就是新年了。


389
00:26:56.640 --> 00:26:57.808
I'm sober now.
我现在清醒了。


390
00:26:58.016 --> 00:26:58.851
I'm sober now.
我现在清醒了。


391
00:26:59.117 --> 00:27:00.694
You got some peaches?
你有桃子吗？


392
00:27:04.340 --> 00:27:07.751
Story going around is you was over there in the big one.
听说你曾经在美国陆军第一师服役过。


393
00:27:08.360 --> 00:27:10.821
How long you fight? Few months? A year?
你打过多长时间的仗？几个月？一年？


394
00:27:12.364 --> 00:27:15.075
I'm a veteran myself, Navy.
我也是退伍老兵，我是海军。


395
00:27:15.242 --> 00:27:17.578
Spanish-American War.
我参加过美西战争。


396
00:27:17.744 --> 00:27:19.580
Of course, the ass we kicked only took one day.
当然了，我们只花了一天时间就打赢了。


397
00:27:19.746 --> 00:27:23.083
Steamed into Manila Bay May 1, 1898,

398
00:27:23.250 --> 00:27:27.588
aboard the gunboat Concord under old George Dewey.
乘坐康科德号战列舰驶入马尼拉湾。


399
00:27:27.754 --> 00:27:32.759
Set them 8-inch guns a-blazing till smoke blotted out the sun.
让8英寸口径的大炮开火，直到烟雾遮住太阳。


400
00:27:32.926 --> 00:27:36.013
Sunk the Spanish fleet,steamed out May 2.
击沉西班牙舰队，他们于5月2日撤离。


401
00:27:42.269 --> 00:27:45.105
Only eight Americans got wounded.
只有8名美国人受伤。


402
00:27:45.272 --> 00:27:47.733
I had the audacity to be one of them.
我有胆量成为他们中的一员，


403
00:27:49.276 --> 00:27:52.112
Where were you? France?
你在哪里参战的？法国？


404
00:27:52.279 --> 00:27:54.298
Put my foots in Germany, too.
我也踏足过德国。


405
00:27:54.364 --> 00:27:55.340
Germany?
德国？


406
00:27:55.407 --> 00:27:57.342
I'd like to see the Kaiser's face...
我真想去看看德皇的脸...


407
00:27:57.409 --> 00:28:00.120
when you come runnin' out of the Black Forest.
当你们从黑森林中出现时。


408
00:28:00.287 --> 00:28:02.122
We didn't have no coloreds on the Concord.
我们的康科德号上没有有色人种。


409
00:28:02.289 --> 00:28:04.124
Whole ship full of good ol' boys.
整艘船都是好孩子。


410
00:28:04.291 --> 00:28:05.626
Wouldn't have took to it.
你也许不喜欢这个。


411
00:28:05.793 --> 00:28:07.169
Maybe.
可能吧。


412
00:28:08.504 --> 00:28:10.589
The mortars start flyin',
迫击炮开始轰鸣


413
00:28:10.756 --> 00:28:13.091
the gas start blowin',
硝烟弥漫，


414
00:28:13.258 --> 00:28:15.010
there ain't much color in them trenches.
战壕里没有多少有色人种。


415
00:28:15.177 --> 00:28:16.637
Is that right?
真的吗？


416
00:28:16.804 --> 00:28:18.472
You got them.45s?
你有点45的手枪子弹吗？


417
00:28:18.639 --> 00:28:22.101
.45s. Funny thing about the draft.
点45子弹。征兵处在开玩笑吧。


418
00:28:22.267 --> 00:28:24.603
I can't understand it. Pull a colored boy out of his home,
我不明白。把一个黑人男孩从家里拉出来，


419
00:28:24.770 --> 00:28:28.148
send him over there, tell him dig trenches, kill white folks.
派他上战场，告诉他挖战壕，杀白人。


420
00:28:28.315 --> 00:28:30.734
That seem right to you?
你就是这样吧？


421
00:28:30.901 --> 00:28:34.279
I wouldn't know much about that, sir.
我对此了解不多，先生。


422
00:28:34.446 --> 00:28:36.740
I volunteered.
我是自愿参军的。


423
00:29:45.809 --> 00:29:47.978
You been double-timing me.
你一直在敷衍我。


424
00:29:52.274 --> 00:29:55.903
Seeing that married Miz Connelly over in Wylie.
看到那个在怀利的已婚妇女，米兹.康纳利吗？


425
00:30:00.282 --> 00:30:01.450
I know.
我知道。


426
00:30:06.288 --> 00:30:08.123
Where you going?
你要去哪里？


427
00:30:08.290 --> 00:30:10.000
Back to work.
回去工作。


428
00:30:11.293 --> 00:30:13.629
Don't you turn your back on me...
不许你背对着我...


429
00:30:13.796 --> 00:30:15.672
when I talk!
尤其在我讲话时！


430
00:30:20.302 --> 00:30:22.638
Damn swamp tramp!
骚娘们儿！


431
00:30:22.805 --> 00:30:24.181
What you crying about?
你为什么哭？


432
00:30:24.348 --> 00:30:27.518
What you think you're doing, hitting me?
你认为你在干什么？想打我吗？


433
00:30:27.684 --> 00:30:29.645
You little swamp tramp!
你这个小骚货！


434
00:30:29.853 --> 00:30:31.814
You little swamp tramp!
小骚逼！


435
00:30:31.980 --> 00:30:33.440
Huh? You little chigger!
呃？你个小臭虫！


436
00:30:33.607 --> 00:30:35.692
You don't hit me!
你别想打我！


437
00:30:35.859 --> 00:30:36.860
You don't hit me!
别想打我！


438
00:30:38.862 --> 00:30:40.239
You don't hit me!
你别想打我！


439
00:30:41.323 --> 00:30:42.825
Girl...
丫头...


440
00:30:44.159 --> 00:30:46.036
Get out! Get out!
滚出去！滚出去！


441
00:30:46.203 --> 00:30:47.538
Get out!
滚！


442
00:31:01.844 --> 00:31:03.178
Philomena!
费罗米娜！


443
00:31:15.732 --> 00:31:17.192
M-Miz Taylor?
泰勒小姐？


444
00:31:17.401 --> 00:31:20.112
Is you all right, ma'am?
你没事吗？夫人？


445
00:31:22.739 --> 00:31:24.658
Go away, Philomena.
走开，费罗米娜。


446
00:31:24.825 --> 00:31:26.743
B-But...
但，但是...


447
00:31:26.910 --> 00:31:28.287
Get out.
出去。


448
00:31:28.454 --> 00:31:29.872
Get out!
出去！


449
00:31:37.921 --> 00:31:39.981
So you fight in the war?
那么说你打过仗？


450
00:31:41.675 --> 00:31:43.218
Kill anybody over there?
在战场上杀过人吗？


451
00:31:44.970 --> 00:31:46.930
I mostly dug trenches.
我主要是在挖战壕。


452
00:31:48.390 --> 00:31:51.226
Still, it must've been grand seeing Chicago...
不过，能看到芝加哥一定很壮观…


453
00:31:51.393 --> 00:31:52.519
and New York.
还能看到纽约。


454
00:31:53.896 --> 00:31:56.106
Shoot, I ain't been nowhere but Rosewood,
我呀，连紫檀镇都没离开过，


455
00:31:56.273 --> 00:31:58.208
Sumner, Cedar Key,
还有就是萨姆纳，雪松树，


456
00:31:58.275 --> 00:32:00.527
three times to Gainesville.
我就去过盖恩斯维尔三趟。


457
00:32:00.694 --> 00:32:02.738
Why you come back south?
你为什么来我们南方？


458
00:32:02.905 --> 00:32:04.323
Maybe...
也许...


459
00:32:06.450 --> 00:32:08.535
I was looking for Rosewood.
我和紫檀镇有缘。


460
00:32:15.667 --> 00:32:16.668
Thank you.
谢谢你。


461
00:32:19.129 --> 00:32:23.050
Well, how come you ain't never settled down before now?
那你怎么一直没安定下来呢？


462
00:32:24.301 --> 00:32:26.053
I was married...
我结过婚...


463
00:32:28.388 --> 00:32:29.389
once.
就一次。


464
00:32:34.895 --> 00:32:37.564
My Aunt Sarah, she say I ask too many questions.
我的萨拉阿姨，她总说我爱问很多问题。


465
00:32:37.731 --> 00:32:38.774
I'm sorry if...
我很抱歉，如果...


466
00:32:41.944 --> 00:32:43.529
How old you be,Scrappie?
你多大了？斯卡比。


467
00:32:43.695 --> 00:32:45.280
I'm 17.
我17了。


468
00:32:45.447 --> 00:32:46.824
No man?
还没男人吧？


469
00:32:48.075 --> 00:32:49.535
- No young ones?- No.
-也没有小孩吗？-没有啦。


470
00:32:51.370 --> 00:32:54.832
I just take care of my little cousins, though.
我还在照看我的小表弟。


471
00:32:58.460 --> 00:32:59.753
Come on.
来吧。


472
00:33:01.296 --> 00:33:02.798
Come on.
来吧。


473
00:33:02.965 --> 00:33:04.383
Where you going?
你去哪里？


474
00:33:08.679 --> 00:33:11.014
What you think about this land here?
你觉得这块地怎么样？


475
00:33:11.181 --> 00:33:14.017
Well, I...I likes it fine.
那么，我...我喜欢它，很好。


476
00:33:14.184 --> 00:33:15.644
Mr. Wright...
但是，赖特先生...


477
00:33:15.811 --> 00:33:19.731
He going to buy it, though. He buying up everything.
他想买下这块地。他要买下一切。


478
00:33:20.983 --> 00:33:22.276
Maybe.
也许吧。


479
00:33:49.720 --> 00:33:50.721
Hey, anybody!
嘿，有人在家吗！


480
00:33:51.805 --> 00:33:53.223
Hey, boy!
嘿，孩子！


481
00:33:56.018 --> 00:33:58.353
Yes, sir.
是的，先生。


482
00:33:58.520 --> 00:33:59.913
You a traveling man?
你接待过路人吗？


483
00:34:02.357 --> 00:34:04.359
Who asking, sir?
你在问谁？先生？


484
00:34:22.544 --> 00:34:23.879
We gots to help him.
我们得去帮他。


485
00:34:24.046 --> 00:34:25.130
He ain't our problem.
他不关我们的事。


486
00:34:25.297 --> 00:34:27.382
He a Mason,took the oath, same as us.
他是共济会成员，宣过誓的，跟我们一样。


487
00:34:27.549 --> 00:34:28.967
He's a white Mason.
他是白人共济会的。


488
00:34:31.970 --> 00:34:33.889
Do you think he'd help you?
你认为他会帮助你吗？


489
00:34:34.056 --> 00:34:35.307
Aaron, boy, I swear,
阿伦，孩子，我发誓，


490
00:34:35.474 --> 00:34:38.310
sometimes you ain't got more sense than some of these horses.
有时候你还不如这些马有见识。


491
00:34:38.477 --> 00:34:39.937
Now, I'm telling you...
现在，我告诉你...


492
00:34:41.772 --> 00:34:43.190
that man...
那个人...


493
00:34:43.357 --> 00:34:45.317
he ain't nothing but trouble.
他就是在找麻烦。


494
00:34:46.401 --> 00:34:47.903
Yeah, well, let me tell you something.
好吧，让我告诉你。


495
00:34:48.070 --> 00:34:49.238
See, I ain't no boy.
你看，我不是小孩子。


496
00:34:49.404 --> 00:34:51.573
See, I's a man.
你看，我是个男人。


497
00:34:51.740 --> 00:34:53.408
I's a Mason.
是个共济会成员。


498
00:34:53.575 --> 00:34:55.077
What you be, Sam?
你看你这样，萨姆？


499
00:35:03.335 --> 00:35:05.504
Everybody sit down.Let's get this done.
大家都坐下。让我们完成这事。


500
00:35:05.571 --> 00:35:06.939
Bradley, you got the deed?
布莱德利，你的房契呢？


501
00:35:07.005 --> 00:35:09.967
Uh, yes, sir, I do, Mr. Andrews.
是的，安德鲁斯先生，我带了。


502
00:35:12.803 --> 00:35:16.390
No, no, boy,I haven't paid for it yet.
不，不，孩子，我还没付钱呢。


503
00:35:16.557 --> 00:35:18.559
We got to sell it first.
我们得先把它卖掉。


504
00:35:18.725 --> 00:35:21.687
Here. Give it here.Give it here, boy.
这儿，交到这儿来，孩子。


505
00:35:23.689 --> 00:35:26.525
We gots here 5 acres in Rosewood...
我们要对紫檀镇的5英亩土地...


506
00:35:26.692 --> 00:35:28.527
adjacent to Mr. Johnny Wright's store...
它靠近约翰尼.赖特先生的商店...


507
00:35:28.694 --> 00:35:30.195
sold as is,cash only.
如约出售，只收现金。


508
00:35:30.362 --> 00:35:32.130
Let's open up at $52 an acre.
让我们先以每亩52美元开价。


509
00:35:32.197 --> 00:35:35.659
52, 52. Who'll give me 52 down front?

510
00:35:35.826 --> 00:35:37.161
53, 53, 53 from Monroe.

511
00:35:37.369 --> 00:35:39.246
54, 54, 54.

512
00:35:39.413 --> 00:35:40.247
Who'll give me 54?
有谁出54元？


513
00:35:40.414 --> 00:35:42.124
54, 54.

514
00:35:42.291 --> 00:35:44.251
John Wright again.Thank you, John.
约翰.怀特又出价了。谢谢你，约翰。


515
00:35:44.418 --> 00:35:46.503
55, 55.

516
00:35:46.670 --> 00:35:48.922
55, anybody? Monroe, 55?

517
00:35:50.115 --> 00:35:51.191
$54.

518
00:35:51.258 --> 00:35:52.718
Going once,going twice...
一次，两次...


519
00:35:52.885 --> 00:35:54.595
$55.

520
00:35:56.972 --> 00:35:59.391
Boy, you know that's $55 for each acre?
伙计，你知道那是每英亩55美元吗？


521
00:35:59.558 --> 00:36:00.642
That's damn near $300.
那就是共需近300美元。


522
00:36:00.851 --> 00:36:02.895
Yes, sir, I do.
是的，先生，我知道。


523
00:36:03.061 --> 00:36:04.021
Thank you kindly.
谢谢你的好意。


524
00:36:04.188 --> 00:36:05.439
Cash?
现金？


525
00:36:08.901 --> 00:36:10.861
Where's that nigger going to get that kind of money?
那个黑鬼从哪儿弄到那么多钱？


526
00:36:14.031 --> 00:36:15.365
I have $55.
我有55美元。


527
00:36:52.611 --> 00:36:54.571
Get back to work.
继续干活。


528
00:37:16.677 --> 00:37:19.221
Afternoon, Miss Fanny.
下午好，范妮小姐。


529
00:37:24.226 --> 00:37:25.227
Help!
救命！


530
00:37:25.394 --> 00:37:26.895
Help me!
帮帮我！


531
00:37:27.104 --> 00:37:29.940
Somebody please help me!
请来人帮帮我！


532
00:37:30.149 --> 00:37:31.358
Somebody!
来人啊！


533
00:37:31.525 --> 00:37:32.776
Help me!
救我！


